DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-0.059ft at 06:48\n-2.936ft at 10:06\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Slow fading blend of WNW and SSW swell is still good for thigh-waist-stoma
 ch high surf in the morning then waves gradually wind down during the day.
   Draining dawn patrol negative low tide\, then incoming tide push helps f
 irst half of the morning. Mid day and evening high tides bog down tide sen
 sitive breaks. \n\nLight/variable morning winds\, followed by a light SW a
 fternoon sea breeze. 
